1.0.0 · [source](about:blank/src/std/io/mod.rs.html#2795-2797)

Returns the number of bytes that can be read before this instance will return EOF.

##### [§](#note)Note

This instance may reach `EOF` after reading fewer bytes than indicated by this method if the underlying [`Read`](trait.Read.html "trait std::io::Read") instance reaches EOF.

##### [§](#examples)Examples

```
use std::io;
use std::io::prelude::*;
use std::fs::File;

fn main() -> io::Result<()> {
    let f = File::open("foo.txt")?;

    // read at most five bytes
    let handle = f.take(5);

    println!("limit: {}", handle.limit());
    Ok(())
}
```

