1.20.0 · [source](about:blank/src/std/io/mod.rs.html#2902-2904)

Gets a mutable reference to the underlying reader.

Care should be taken to avoid modifying the internal I/O state of the underlying reader as doing so may corrupt the internal limit of this `Take`.

##### [§](#examples-4)Examples

```
use std::io;
use std::io::prelude::*;
use std::fs::File;

fn main() -> io::Result<()> {
    let mut file = File::open("foo.txt")?;

    let mut buffer = [0; 5];
    let mut handle = file.take(5);
    handle.read(&mut buffer)?;

    let file = handle.get_mut();
    Ok(())
}
```

